items.title: Slammin' Braves chase Max, reward Gohara
items.summary: In just his second career start, Braves left-hander Luiz Gohara went toe-to-toe with Nationals right-hander Max Scherzer, the favorite to win his second consecutive National League Cy Young Award. Then, Atlanta broke out for six runs in the seventh -- highlighted by a grand slam by Matt Kemp -- to cruise to an 8-2 victory Wednesday night at Nationals Park.

items.title: Owings hopes to help D-backs come October
items.summary: Watching his teammates position themselves for the postseason has been a joy for D-backs shortstop Chris Owings. Not being able to contribute since fracturing his right middle finger on July 30, however, has been agony.
